Cursor-Specific Project Rules:

Follow PEP8 standards for all Python code

Document each function with a clear docstring describing its purpose, inputs, and outputs

Use Git for version control, and regularly commit changes

Run linting (e.g., flake8) on the code to ensure it’s clean and follows standards

Write unit tests for all critical functions (strategy logic, risk management, execution)

Use a .env file for securely storing API keys and avoid exposing them in the code

Implement error handling for common issues like API errors, high volatility, and connection issues

Paper trade for at least 100 simulated trades before live trading